mp3guessenc
------------------------------------------
Small utility for analyzing audio mpeg files and detecting the encoder used
(when layer III)

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/mp3guessenc/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/mp3guessenc/mp3guessenc-0.27.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mp3guessenc-0.27.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mp3guessenc-0.27.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mp3guessenc-0.27.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mp3guessenc-0.27.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(mp3guessenc)
  /usr/bin/mp3guessenc.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/mp3guessenc.README
  /usr/share/doc/mp3guessenc/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/mp3guessenc/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/mp3guessenc/DOCS
  /usr/share/doc/mp3guessenc/TODO

------------------

